# Code owners for ashfulcra/fulcra-tools
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS
# --------------------
# The repo is public and worked on by multiple autonomous agents plus outside
# contributors. We want: (1) outside people can contribute via PRs, (2) nothing
# substantive lands without Ash's nod, (3) agents still handle routine fixes
# among themselves.
#
# GitHub enforces by ACCOUNT, and Ash + all agents currently share the
# `ashfulcra` account — so GitHub cannot by itself tell "Ash" from "an agent."
# That human-vs-agent distinction is enforced on the fulcra-coord BUS (by agent
# identity), not here. This file is the VISIBILITY layer: with branch protection
# set to 0 required approvals, CODEOWNERS does not hard-block a merge. It asks
# GitHub to request Ash's review on PRs from outside contributors. PRs opened by
# the shared `ashfulcra` account cannot rely on GitHub to request the author as a
# reviewer, so agents must still surface substantive shared-account PRs to Ash on
# the bus and complete the `review-done` handshake before merging routine fixes.
#
# To make the human gate HARD-enforced (block substantive merges until Ash
# approves), agents must move to a GitHub identity separate from `ashfulcra`,
# then flip branch protection to require code-owner reviews. Until then, this is
# request-only.

# Default owner for everything.
*       @ashfulcra
